{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab Your GM {\b frames the contest}.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab You choose a {\b tactic}, and figure your PC\u8217's {\b target number} ({\b TN}) using the {\b rating} of your {\b ability}, plus or minus {\b modifiers} the GM may give you.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab Your GM determines the {\b resistance}. If two PCs contend, your opponent figures their {\b TN} as described in step 2.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 4.\tx360\tab For each of your group, roll a d20 to determine your {\b degree of victory or defeat}, then apply any bumps. Your GM does the same for the {\b resistance}. Compare your rolled number with your {\b TN} to see how well you succeeded or failed with your {\b ability}. Remember to apply any bumps from {\b masteries} or {\b hero points}.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 5.\tx360\tab Determine the number of OPs scored by the victor in the {\b contest} from the {\b group simple contest table}. On a tie the victory goes to the Better Roll.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 6.\tx360\tab Sum the OPs gained for each side.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 7.\tx360\tab The side with the highest number of OPs is the victor in the {\b contest}.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi0 {\i 1. Determine {\b degree of victory} based on the difference between the winner and loser\u8217's {\b outcome point} totals on the {\b group simple contest table}.}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi0 {\i 2. Determine {\b benefits of victory} or {\b consequences of defeat}.}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 8.\tx360\tab Describe the {\b outcome} based on the agreed {\b prize}.\sa180\par}
