{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 For the final, climactic confrontation that wraps up your GM\u8217's story, your GM uses the following, more punishing method of doling out consequences. This represents that at the climax you may triumph, but be laid low by the effort. At the end of the contest up all {\b resolution points} scored against you by your opponents. If you engage more than one opponent, be sure to add the {\b resolution points} scored against you by all of them. If you lost, add 1 to your total. Your GM cross-references the total against the {\b climactic state of adversity} table.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 As with all {\b contests}, we care about your {\b outcome}, win or lose, and the GM will narrate the {\b outcome} for the {\b resistance}, which may not be symmetrical. Even if you win, you may suffer {\b consequences} as per this table.\par}
